<br>
Raids aren't made for exping however I'm not really too keen on the idea of taking away exp from raid mobs/zones.  True raid only zones, what little there are of them, I could be forgetting but really only ones that come to mind are ToV, ST since other zones still lend themselves to the possibility of exping in a single group.  Exp from raid mobs, normally isn't that noticable anyways.  I don't think the coding for removing exp from raid mobs is valid, and by saying a raid mob I'm refering to the main target.  Saying we are raiding trak, and then all mobs in between us and trak are then tagged raid mobs is not gonna happen, (don't tell me juggs are raid mobs, they can be done by one group.)  Removing exp from just the target mob...fine but again what about the mobs between you and target, there is still the source of the problem with people being able to whine about exp otw to the target then.<br>
